# Mantine v8 UI Rules

Mantine is the ONLY UI library. No Tailwind. No shadcn. No Radix.

## Components

Use Mantine components exclusively:
- Layout: `Stack`, `Group`, `Box`, `Grid`, `Flex`, `Container`, `SimpleGrid`
- Typography: `Text`, `Title`, `Anchor`, `Highlight`
- Inputs: `TextInput`, `NumberInput`, `Select`, `Textarea`, `FileInput`
- Feedback: `Notification`, `Alert`, `Progress`, `Loader`, `Skeleton`
- Overlay: `Modal`, `Drawer`, `Popover`, `Tooltip`, `Menu`
- Data: `Table`, `Badge`, `Card`, `Timeline`
- File upload: `Dropzone` from `@mantine/dropzone`

## Hooks

Use Mantine hooks instead of building your own:
- `useForm` for form state and validation
- `useDisclosure` for open/close state (modals, drawers)
- `useDebouncedValue` for search inputs
- `useMediaQuery` for responsive logic

## Styling

- NEVER write `className="flex"` or any Tailwind utility class
- Use Mantine's `style` prop for one-off styles
- Use CSS Modules (`*.module.css`) for complex/reusable styles
- Use Mantine theme tokens for colors: `var(--mantine-color-teal-6)`, not hardcoded hex
- `sx` prop is REMOVED in v8 — use `style` prop or CSS Modules only
- Use `rem()` from `@mantine/core` for all spacing values in `style` props, never raw px
- Use `c` prop for text color (`c="dimmed"`), never `style={{ color: '...' }}`
- Use `gap` on `Group`/`Stack`, not `spacing`

## Common API Mistakes (v8)

- `Button` loading: use `loading` prop directly — never wrap in a custom spinner
- Forms: always `useForm` from `@mantine/form` — never `react-hook-form` or uncontrolled inputs
- Notifications: always `@mantine/notifications` — never custom toast implementations
- `z-index` max 300 — Mantine modal stack starts at 200; never use `!important`

## Responsive Design

- Mobile-first: base styles for mobile, override upward via Mantine breakpoints
  - xs: 576px · sm: 768px · md: 992px · lg: 1200px · xl: 1400px
- Layout via `<Grid>`, `<Stack>`, `<Group>` — never hardcoded pixel widths
- `useMediaQuery` from `@mantine/hooks` for conditional render logic
- Supplier portal: fully functional on mobile — large touch targets (min 44px), single-column, prominent `<Dropzone>`
- Verification workspace: desktop-primary split-screen at `lg+`; at `md` and below, stack to single column with PDF behind a toggle

## Component Patterns

- Consultant UI is data-dense: `Table` with `stickyHeader`, wrapped in `ScrollArea`, `Badge` for status
- Supplier portal: minimal chrome, one clear action per screen, `<Dropzone>` only — no custom drag-and-drop
- Status indicators MUST combine color + icon + text — never color alone (accessibility)

## Accessibility

- All form fields must have explicit `label` props — placeholder is never a substitute
- Status indicators: combine color + icon + text
- Async updates (extraction pipeline) must use `aria-live` regions
- Interactive elements: min 44px touch target

## Client Directives

- Add `"use client"` only when the component uses Mantine hooks or browser APIs
- Server Components should remain the default
- `MantineProvider` and context providers go in a client boundary wrapper, never directly in a Server Component

## Hard Bans

- No Tailwind classes
- No `!important`
- No `z-index` above 300
- No `useEffect` for data that can be server-fetched
- No custom drag-and-drop — use `@mantine/dropzone`
- No `react-hook-form` — use `@mantine/form`
- No custom toast/notification UI — use `@mantine/notifications`
